<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9769391417897></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9769391417897><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=9769391417897>RE: Trade skills?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=9769391417897#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Dec 16th 3:59 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As bards we go everywhere.&nbsp;&nbsp;Start with fishing and foraging bank the fish and foraged.  When you max forage and get fishing to 100 then move to tailoring if you have not already.  Use the banked goods to lvl brewing to 62 then sell koalas to tailors(some quest items too).  This is a money maker in bursts as needed.  Skills under 100 in most skills will not roll the money in.   If you are in a Guild then you may not wish to lvl in all the skills and just focus on 1 that can help your guild.  Use your lvl11 song on merchants and get a bag of Chr items.  I payed for Chr items in a week in profits. <br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
