<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9768908218032></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9768908218032><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=9768908218032>RE: can bards tank any good</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=9768908218032#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Dec 15th 2:33 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.33]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Of course bards can solo!&nbsp;&nbsp;I'm a level 11 woodelf bard and i'm soloing Caimans in the oasis.  A High level buff always helps you to handle the reds and yellows you come across.  When I solo i usually keep Anthem De Arms on so i hit for max Dmg.  A good weapon helps out alot.  I'm am running around with a Sharkjaw Cutlass thit hits for 21 dmg max, It cost me about 50pp, that is when it is at it's cheapest.  Armor helps alot, banded armor is good for now, they sell for about 1pp per Ac, its the same with bronze, but go with bronze as soon as you can.  Goodluck!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
