	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hmm, well what is there to say...hehe<br>The bard is (Im my eyes) the most fun class to play, diverse and rather difficult to play solo...<br>To yer problem Gaul, the hymn of restoration taunts the mob as if you where hitting it fer the same ammount of damage as you heal (an example to this: say that you heal fer 10 points of hp per tick, in a full group this equals a blow of 60 dmg, and this affects all the mobs around you of the same type) No wonder they get angry at ya! :)<br>My advice is to tell this to the group, and add that the tanks should hit taund like a madman to keep em off you, if this doesnt help, turn off the Hymn fer a couple of ticks, allowing the tanks to become the main target of the mob again...<br>If nothing else helps and youre stuck in a multiple mob situation, hit scelos and 'run' the exess mobs til yer group is ready fer the rest (do NOT do this in a dungeon or tunnel as youll attract even more mobs...*shivers of the thought of personal experience*)<br><br>Best of luck to ya all out there, take care and be safe :)<br><br>Luicid Dreaming<br>Bard of the 33 song of the Innorouk server...<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
